decks.notes: This deck revolves around using various artifacts and lands to generate mana and create a powerful board presence. The key strategy involves assembling specific combinations of cards, such as The One Ring and Blade of the Bloodchief, to fuel powerful creatures like Glaring Fleshraker and Basking Broodscale. By using cards like Springleaf Drum and Grove of the Burnwillows to ramp up mana quickly, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with big threats early in the game. The inclusion of cards like Pithing Needle and Boseiju, Who Endures provides additional utility and protection for the combo pieces.

The deck focuses on controlling the opponent's actions and resources through a combination of counterspells, removal spells, and disruptive creatures. It employs graveyard recursion with Unearth and Thought Scour to maintain card advantage and tempo. The creatures in the deck serve multiple purposes, such as disrupting the opponent's strategy or providing card advantage. The mana base is designed to support the deck's ability to consistently cast its spells while also providing access to various colors of mana. Overall, the deck aims to outlast the opponent and win through incremental advantage.

This UB Mill deck focuses on quickly milling the opponent's library by using cards like Archive Trap, Fractured Sanity, and Glimpse the Unthinkable while also controlling the board with counterspells like Drown in the Loch and removal spells like Fatal Push and Murderous Cut. The deck also includes cards like Hedron Crab and Ruin Crab to consistently mill the opponent each turn. Surgical Extraction and Crypt Incursion are used to disrupt the opponent's strategy and gain advantage. The deck aims to mill the opponent's library as quickly as possible to win the game.

The deck focuses on cycling creatures and manipulating the graveyard to eventually cast Living End, a powerful sorcery that allows you to return all creature cards from your graveyard to the battlefield. By cycling cards like Striped Riverwinder and Street Wraith, you can quickly fill your graveyard and set up for a game-winning Living End. The deck also utilizes cards like Subtlety and Force of Negation to control the board and protect your combo. Overall, the key concept of the deck is to efficiently cycle through your deck and set up for a devastating Living End resolution.
